Pantheon Version

Given the doctrines you’ve been building, I’d probably formalize it like this:

The Harvester

A Pantheon daemon responsible for cultivating intelligence and information ecosystems.

Role
Signal Cultivation & Yield Optimization

Function
Transform raw information, interactions, experiments, failures, and observations into reusable knowledge assets.

Operational Loop

Scout → Plant → Cultivate → Select → Cross-Pollinate → Harvest → Store → Replant

Works With

* Scarab (recycles waste into nutrients)
* Pinecone (stores dormant seeds)
* Flood Eater (prevents information floods)
* Semantic LiDAR (measures soil depth beneath surface signals)
* Herding Dog (keeps humans from being herded by the system)

Core Principle

“Do not collect data. Cultivate conditions where useful knowledge grows.”

In that framing, an AI farmer isn’t really farming AI. They’re farming the environment that produces intelligence. And a data farmer isn’t collecting information. They’re cultivating fertile ground where information becomes knowledge and knowledge becomes capability.